(laughing)

34:19.375 --> 34:20.708
MATTY: Whoa, look at
the crucible itself.

34:20.833 --> 34:23.125
-TIM: She is red-hot.
-NIKOLINE: Yeah, look out.

34:23.208 --> 34:25.042
-(all exclaiming)
-TIM: You missed it.

34:25.208 --> 34:27.167
-It's okay.
-That's all right.

34:27.250 --> 34:28.708
There's your gold right there.

34:30.500 --> 34:32.125
MATTY:
It's so discolored now.

34:32.250 --> 34:34.458
ROSS: Yes, so now we need
to tap it with a hammer.

34:34.542 --> 34:36.417
TIM:
You chisel off the impurities.

34:37.625 --> 34:38.583
Just like that.

34:41.417 --> 34:43.333
-MATTY: Oh, there it goes.
-TIM: There we go.

34:43.458 --> 34:45.250
-ROSS: (chuckles)
Isn't that something?
-TIM: Put your hand out.

34:45.375 --> 34:48.042
-(sighs) Gold!
-There you go.

34:49.833 --> 34:51.458
-TIM: That's cool, man.
-MATTY: It really is.

34:51.542 --> 34:55.583
I mean, all the work you do,
that is the reward.

34:55.708 --> 34:57.917
And it's awesome
to watch you guys do it.

34:58.042 --> 35:00.667
So, how did it feel
to find that gold,

35:00.792 --> 35:02.125
but then you see it melted?

35:02.208 --> 35:04.000
I think it's just a thrill.

35:04.125 --> 35:05.333
I really do,
I think it's awesome.

35:05.500 --> 35:08.042
Yeah, but we didn't melt
your gold.

35:08.208 --> 35:09.833
-What?
-We saved it.

35:10.000 --> 35:11.208
We couldn't melt
y'all's first gold.

35:11.375 --> 35:12.500
You need to-- let's see here.

35:12.667 --> 35:14.167
-Aw!
-No way. No way.

35:14.250 --> 35:15.750
We couldn't melt
your first pieces you find.

35:15.875 --> 35:17.292
-No way.
-Couldn't do it, guys.
Couldn't do it.

35:17.417 --> 35:18.917
There's the first piece
you found.

35:19.042 --> 35:20.333
-Listen, listen.
-That's so cute.

35:20.417 --> 35:21.708
And there was the piece
that you put in...

35:21.833 --> 35:22.958
-No! Aw!
-There you go, guys.

35:23.083 --> 35:24.917
We couldn't put that
in the fire.

35:25.042 --> 35:26.583
MATTY:
Okay, listen.

35:26.708 --> 35:28.458
-Thank you.
-First of all,
I'm not gonna cry.

35:28.542 --> 35:30.625
'Cause I get emotional
like Rick.

35:32.042 --> 35:33.875
But I am so touched by this.

35:34.000 --> 35:36.667
But I'm gonna--
I'm gonna beg you.

35:36.750 --> 35:40.292
I will take any memento
you want to give me.

35:40.417 --> 35:42.417
Matter of fact,
I want something, I do.

35:42.542 --> 35:43.833
I wanted to bring something
from here to show people

35:43.958 --> 35:45.167
and say I was here.

35:45.250 --> 35:47.625
But I truly want you
to use this.

35:49.417 --> 35:51.167
I want you to use this,
'cause I've been so impressed

35:51.250 --> 35:52.875
by what you guys have done.

35:53.000 --> 35:55.375
I want you to use this to help
fund what you're doing.

35:56.417 --> 35:58.042
You need it.
Your first piece of gold.

35:58.208 --> 35:59.500
You've got to be able
to walk around

35:59.625 --> 36:01.000
and say, "Look here,
look what I found.

36:01.083 --> 36:02.375
-I picked it out."
-That's our gift.

36:02.500 --> 36:03.917
-That's right.
-It means more to us

36:04.042 --> 36:05.458
-that you can keep that.
-We will find more.

36:05.583 --> 36:07.583
-We will find more of that.
-I'm serious, brother.

36:07.708 --> 36:10.042
This is really special.

36:10.167 --> 36:11.667
With the treasure,
I never presume

36:11.792 --> 36:15.083
that I'm gonna get
to keep any of it, ever.

36:15.208 --> 36:17.250
They could use that
and sell that gold,

36:17.375 --> 36:18.917
and use that money
back in their operation,

36:19.042 --> 36:20.375
but they would not have it.

36:20.500 --> 36:22.417
So, to be handed this
and to say,

36:22.542 --> 36:24.542
"Take it, it's yours,"
I mean, that's next-level.

36:24.667 --> 36:28.333
Thank you doesn't seem enough,
but thank you.

36:28.500 --> 36:30.125
-You are certainly welcome.
-Absolutely.

36:30.208 --> 36:31.833
We enjoyed y'all's company.

36:31.917 --> 36:34.208
-Yeah? Can we come back?
-ROSS: Absolutely, please do.

36:34.375 --> 36:35.667
You're welcome back.
Our journey's still going.

36:35.750 --> 36:37.333
You need to come back
to see us, you know.

36:37.458 --> 36:39.000
There's so much more to find.

36:39.083 --> 36:40.417
-Oh, yeah.
-Yeah.

36:41.667 --> 36:43.583
-We found the treasure.
-Yeah, we're finding gold,

36:43.708 --> 36:45.167
and it's a process
that keeps growing

36:45.250 --> 36:46.417
-and getting better.
-Yes.

36:48.083 --> 36:50.500
Every day,
there's new stuff being found.

36:50.667 --> 36:52.833
Every day, there's new ideas
of new tools

36:52.917 --> 36:54.292
and machinery being built.

36:54.375 --> 36:56.125
One day, it'll--
a dream can come true.

36:56.250 --> 36:58.333
-Persistence, my friend.
-That's right.

36:58.417 --> 37:00.375
Well, I'm sure you guys
have some work to do, right?

37:00.500 --> 37:02.792
Yeah, we've got to clean our
tools and things to put away.

37:02.917 --> 37:03.958
All right, let's help you.

37:04.042 --> 37:06.583
All right,
let's do it then.

37:06.708 --> 37:08.458
 

37:18.750 --> 37:20.625
MATTY: I just could not
get here fast enough.

37:20.708 --> 37:23.042
When I saw that gold,
man, I'll tell you what.

37:23.167 --> 37:24.833
-I lost my mind.
-Really?

37:24.917 --> 37:25.833
I lost my mind.

37:25.917 --> 37:27.042
The lure of gold.

37:27.167 --> 37:28.625
All right, well,
give us details.

37:28.708 --> 37:31.125
We know you found some gold.
What does that mean?

37:31.208 --> 37:32.375
-Well...
-RICK: Oh!

37:32.542 --> 37:33.833
-Top pocket find.
-Top pocket find.

37:34.000 --> 37:35.875
I learned from Gary Drayton
where to keep it.

37:36.000 --> 37:37.333
There you go.

37:40.333 --> 37:43.292
MARTY: Very cool.
Shiny little bugger.

37:43.375 --> 37:45.292
MATTY: And man,
it's a thrill.

37:45.375 --> 37:46.833
-Pretty exciting.
-It's a thrill.

37:46.958 --> 37:48.208
MARTY:
That's not a bad find.

37:48.333 --> 37:50.167
It's a proof of concept,
is what that is.

37:50.333 --> 37:52.417
-Yeah, yeah.
-That's a proof of concept.

37:52.542 --> 37:54.375
So, what do they want to do?
What are they gonna do next?

37:54.500 --> 37:56.625
Well, I actually
have them standing by,

37:56.708 --> 37:59.167
and I think they have
a couple updates, too.

37:59.292 --> 38:00.625
-Okay.
-I know they want to talk to you

38:00.708 --> 38:02.333
for another reason, too,
but I'll--

38:02.500 --> 38:03.458
-I'll let them explain that.
-MARTY: All right.

38:03.542 --> 38:05.792
-Let's do it.
-Okay, right.

38:06.833 --> 38:09.292
-RICK: Hi, guys.
-MARTY: Hey, Tim. Hey, Ross.

38:09.417 --> 38:10.917
-Hey, how you doing?
-Hey, what's up, guys?

38:11.042 --> 38:13.000
Good to see you again.

38:13.167 --> 38:15.250
Well, guys, what an adventure.

38:15.375 --> 38:17.917
My heart is still in
North Carolina with you boys.

38:18.042 --> 38:19.625
What a time, I just--

38:19.708 --> 38:21.792
I could just say
thank you a million times.

38:21.875 --> 38:23.667
Unbelievable experience.

38:23.792 --> 38:25.792
We hated you left,
we wanted you to stay, man.

38:25.875 --> 38:27.667
We had lots to show you.

38:27.750 --> 38:30.167
Well, I also did
a little messenger service,

38:30.292 --> 38:32.292
and I brought
the package with me

38:32.375 --> 38:34.125
from North Carolina
that you asked me to bring.

38:34.208 --> 38:36.458
-Cool!
-Yeah.

38:36.542 --> 38:37.750
-You ready?
-Yes, hell yeah.

38:37.875 --> 38:38.833
Here you go.

38:39.000 --> 38:40.083
From our new friends

38:40.208 --> 38:41.917
-down South.
-Wow!

38:43.042 --> 38:44.542
MARTY:
Geez, didn't expect that.

38:50.208 --> 38:51.833
MATTY:
From our new friends

38:52.000 --> 38:52.875
-down South.
-Wow!

38:53.042 --> 38:53.958
One for each of you.

38:55.875 --> 38:57.542
MARTY:
Wow.

38:57.667 --> 39:00.125
I see a bunch
of gold in here.

39:00.208 --> 39:01.917
Jeez, didn't expect that.

39:03.750 --> 39:05.292
MATTY: And tell them
what it is, fellas.

39:05.417 --> 39:08.625
It is some gold
from our area, off the dredge.

39:09.542 --> 39:11.125
That's authentic, it is real,

39:11.208 --> 39:15.333
as well as a nail
or a spike that they used

39:15.458 --> 39:17.250
to put down the deck boards.

39:17.375 --> 39:18.458
-MARTY: Very cool.
-RICK: Yeah.

39:18.542 --> 39:20.208
And then, there's a cable
off it too?

39:20.333 --> 39:21.542
Is that what I'm looking at?

39:21.667 --> 39:23.333
TIM: Yes.
In a dredge pile,

39:23.500 --> 39:25.417
we saw this cable sticking up.

39:25.542 --> 39:28.042
And so, I thought,
how cool would that be

39:28.167 --> 39:29.583
to give you guys a taste?

39:29.708 --> 39:31.417
RICK:
This is really cool.

39:33.167 --> 39:34.583
You know what, not many people

39:34.708 --> 39:36.000
have one of these,
I'll tell you.

39:36.167 --> 39:38.167
You're right about that.

39:38.292 --> 39:40.417
-(laughter)
-Yeah, I bet I am, I bet I am.

39:40.542 --> 39:43.458
Have you been doing any work
since I left?

39:43.542 --> 39:45.500
Oh, yeah, yeah,
we've done pretty good.

39:45.625 --> 39:47.667
-Every day.
-We always get some--

39:47.792 --> 39:49.583
I don't know if you can
see it or not.

39:49.708 --> 39:51.417
-There's some gold right there.
-Oh, yeah, we can see it.

39:51.542 --> 39:53.000
Just a few little--
a picker and a nugget.

39:53.125 --> 39:56.042
We've got a vial with some gold.
I know it's hard to see,

39:56.208 --> 39:58.208
-but there's gold in there.
-Oh, no.

39:58.333 --> 39:59.792
We're also working
on a wash plant, you know.

39:59.917 --> 40:02.333
We were just getting that
together,

40:02.417 --> 40:04.083
and we will be able
to run more material...

40:04.208 --> 40:05.458
-Faster.
-...faster,

40:05.583 --> 40:08.333
but to also be able
to separate out

40:08.458 --> 40:11.167
any kind of artifacts,
so that we make sure

40:11.292 --> 40:13.500
-we don't miss any.
-Yes.

40:13.667 --> 40:15.583
You didn't retire
Franken-sluice, did you?

40:15.708 --> 40:17.333
(laughs)

40:17.458 --> 40:18.500
We still got old Franken-sluice
put together.

40:18.667 --> 40:20.208
That's all we've got right now,

40:20.333 --> 40:21.917
but we're working
towards bigger things.

40:22.042 --> 40:24.542
-MARTY: All righty.
-We're trying to find anything

40:24.708 --> 40:27.375
that pertain to artifacts
off the dredge.

40:27.542 --> 40:29.333
That's extremely
important to us.

40:29.458 --> 40:32.833
Is there a way that
that could detected...

40:32.917 --> 40:34.542
Other than just
our metal detectors?

40:34.708 --> 40:36.208
-Yeah, just our metal detectors.
-Oh, yeah.

40:36.375 --> 40:38.542
You'd want--
No, you'd want a magnetometer.

40:38.708 --> 40:40.292
And it could detect things
quite deep.

40:40.417 --> 40:41.750
-On a drone?
-Put it on a drone.

40:41.875 --> 40:43.542
-On a drone.
-Oh, wow, that would be cool.

40:43.667 --> 40:45.167
That would be awesome.

40:45.292 --> 40:47.917
You could actually fly the drone
down inside the compartment.

40:48.042 --> 40:49.375
MATTY:
Yes, you could.

40:49.500 --> 40:51.000
We could fix you up
with one, actually.

40:51.125 --> 40:52.375
We got that equipment.

40:52.500 --> 40:54.833
-Wow. Wow, man, that's crazy.
-(laughs)

40:54.958 --> 40:56.458
Awesome.

40:56.542 --> 40:58.625
All righty, it's been fun
interacting with you.

40:58.750 --> 41:00.875
We'd like to get down
and actually maybe drink a beer

41:01.042 --> 41:02.625
or something with you guys,
it'd be really nice.

41:02.750 --> 41:04.333
-Please, come back.
-That'd be awesome.

41:04.417 --> 41:06.292
-Please come back and see us.
-I'm thirsty.

41:06.417 --> 41:09.333
(laughter)

41:09.458 --> 41:11.458
Thank you, guys.
Thank you for everything,

41:11.542 --> 41:13.167
and we'll-we'll be in touch.

41:13.292 --> 41:15.708
-Y'all come back.
-You hear?

41:15.875 --> 41:17.208
-TIM: You hear?
-See ya, take care, guys.

41:17.333 --> 41:18.667
RICK:
Thanks, guys.

41:19.917 --> 41:21.208
-This is really cool.
-That's above and beyond.

41:21.333 --> 41:22.792
-Isn't that nice?
-Yeah.

41:22.917 --> 41:24.708
-They are gentlemen.
-MARTY: Yeah, they are.

41:26.500 --> 41:27.667
I hope the sight
of gold in your hands

41:27.750 --> 41:29.667
inspired you a little bit,
maybe.

41:29.792 --> 41:32.000
Yeah, I'd like to hold
a little bit more in my hands.

41:32.167 --> 41:33.667
-Yeah.
-When do we get to this?

41:33.792 --> 41:35.500
RICK: The inspiration
really comes from...

41:35.625 --> 41:39.708
Look, they took a--
just a dream, an idea,

41:39.833 --> 41:42.083
and look where they sit,
you know?

41:42.208 --> 41:44.208
Yeah, they're having fun, too,
that's great.

41:44.333 --> 41:47.417
It's not just the concept
of what they're trying to do.

41:47.542 --> 41:49.333
It's the fact that
they are both dedicated

41:49.500 --> 41:52.000
-to telling the story.
-Yeah.

41:52.083 --> 41:55.542
Well, let's go find
about 200,000 of these...

41:55.708 --> 41:56.750
-Yeah.
-...right out there.

41:56.875 --> 41:58.375
-All right, Matty Blake.
-Come on.

41:58.542 --> 42:01.250
-Or more.
-The bar is set pretty low.

42:01.375 --> 42:02.833
MATTY:
200 million. (laughs)

